                    <msContents>
                        <summary>A woodblock printed work on military medicine including treating gunshot wounds and other injuries likely to be incurred in battle, bandaging techniques and other conditions such as food poisoning and cholera, published in two parts in 1853 and 1857. The author, Hirano Genryō (1790-1867), studied medicine in Edo under Taki Motoyasu and published a number of medical works in the closing years of the Edo period.</summary>

